="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"><CHAR>미분방정식의 해는</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="13" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="13" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="15" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"><PICTURE Reverse="false"><SHAPEOBJECT InstId="1930157560" Lock="false" NumberingType="Figure" TextFlow="BothSides" ZOrder="73"><SIZE Height="26944" HeightRelTo="Absolute" Protect="false" Width="26374" WidthRelTo="Absolute"/><POSITION AffectLSpacing="false" AllowOverlap="true" FlowWithText="true" HoldAnchorAndSO="false" HorzAlign="Left" HorzOffset="11370" HorzRelTo="Paper" TreatAsChar="true" VertAlign="Top" VertOffset="70943" VertRelTo="Paper"/><OUTSIDEMARGIN Bottom="0" Left="0" Right="0" Top="0"/><SHAPECOMMENT>그림입니다.
원본 그림의 이름: phase-portrait.png
원본 그림의 크기: 가로 746pixel, 세로 762pixel</SHAPECOMMENT></SHAPEOBJECT><SHAPECOMPONENT CurHeight="26944" CurWidth="26374" GroupLevel="0" HorzFlip="false" InstID="856415737" OriHeight="13245" OriWidth="12965" VertFlip="false" XPos="0" YPos="0"><ROTATIONINFO Angle="0" CenterX="13187" CenterY="13472"/><RENDERINGINFO><TRANSMATRIX E1="1.00000" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="1.00000" E6="0.00000"/><SCAMATRIX E1="2.03425" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="2.03428" E6="0.00000"/><ROTMATRIX E1="1.00000" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="1.00000" E6="0.00000"/></RENDERINGINFO></SHAPECOMPONENT><IMAGERECT X0="0" X1="12965" X2="12965" X3="0" Y0="0" Y1="0" Y2="13245" Y3="13245"/><IMAGECLIP Bottom="57180" Left="0" Right="55980" Top="0"/><INSIDEMARGIN Bottom="0" Left="0" Right="0" Top="0"/><IMAGE Alpha="0" BinItem="4" Bright="0" Contrast="0" Effect="RealPic"/><EFFECTS/></PICTURE><CHAR/></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="15" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="15" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="15" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>예 3) (Solow's model of economic growth)</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="20" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>The following model generalizes the one in </CHAR><FIELDBEGIN Command="https\://mjo.osborne.economics.utoronto.ca/index.php/tutorial/index/1/deq/SEP\#m\:solow;1;0;0;" Dirty="true" Editable="false" InstId="1946448478" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="23"><CHAR>an earlier example</CHAR><FIELDEND Editable="false" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>. Suppose that the production function is an increasing and </CHAR><FIELDBEGIN Command="https\://mjo.osborne.economics.utoronto.ca/index.php/tutorial/index/1/deq/CVN\#d\:strCcv;1;0;0;" Dirty="true" Editable="false" InstId="1946448479" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="23"><CHAR>strictly concave</CHAR><FIELDEND Editable="false" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> function </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> that is </CHAR><FIELDBEGIN Command="https\://mjo.osborne.economics.utoronto.ca/index.php/tutorial/index/1/deq/HOM\#d\:hom1;1;0;0;" Dirty="true" Editable="false" InstId="1946448480" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="23"><CHAR>homogeneous of degree 1</CHAR><FIELDEND Editable="false" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> (i.e. has “constant returns to scale”), rather than taking the specific form assumed in the earlier example. Assume also that </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(0, </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>) = 0 for all </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> (no output can be produced without any capital).</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>Example (Solow's model of economic growth)</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="20" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>Output is produced from capital, denoted </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>, and labor, denoted </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>, according to the production function </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>AK</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>1−</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>, where </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>A</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> is a positive constant and 0 &lt; </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> &lt; 1. A constant fraction </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> of output is “saved” (with 0 &lt; </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> &lt; 1), and used to augment the capital stock. Thus the capital stock changes according to the differential equation</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>))</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="9"><CHAR>1−</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>))</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>and takes the value </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> at </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> = 0. The labor force is </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> &gt; 0 at </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> = 0 and grows at a constant rate λ, so that</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = λ.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>One way to find a solution of this model is to first solve for </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, then substitute the resulting expression into the equation for </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) and solve for </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>The equation for </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> is separable. Integrating both sides yields ln </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> = λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> + </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>C</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, or </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>Ce</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="9"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>. Given the initial condition, we have </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>C</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Substituting this result into the equation for </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) yields</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><TABLE BorderFill="3" CellSpacing="0" ColCount="3" PageBreak="Cell" RepeatHeader="true" RowCount="2"><SHAPEOBJECT InstId="1946448493" Lock="false" NumberingType="Table" TextWrap="TopAndBottom" ZOrder="141"><SIZE Height="3682" HeightRelTo="Absolute" Protect="false" Width="13350" WidthRelTo="Absolute"/><POSITION AffectLSpacing="false" AllowOverlap="false" FlowWithText="true" HoldAnchorAndSO="false" HorzAlign="Left" HorzOffset="0" HorzRelTo="Para" TreatAsChar="false" VertAlign="Top" VertOffset="0" VertRelTo="Para"/><OUTSIDEMARGIN Bottom="141" Left="141" Right="141" Top="141"/></SHAPEOBJECT><INSIDEMARGIN Bottom="141" Left="510" Right="510" Top="141"/><ROW><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="0" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="1875"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="1" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="1425"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> = </CHAR></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="2" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="10050"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>))</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>1−</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="19"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>e</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"/></P></PARALIST></CELL></ROW><ROW><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="0" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="1" RowSpan="1" Width="1875"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"/></P></PARALIST></CELL><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="1" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="1" RowSpan="1" Width="1425"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> = </CHAR></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="2" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="1" RowSpan="1" Width="10050"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="19"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>e</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>))</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>1−</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL></ROW></TABLE><CHAR/></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>This equation is separable, and may be written as</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>))</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="9"><CHAR>−1</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>e</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="9"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Integrating both sides, we obtain</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>))</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>e</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="9"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>λ + </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>C</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>,</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>so that</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = (</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>e</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="9"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>/λ + </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>C</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="9"><CHAR>1/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Given </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(0) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, we conclude that </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>C</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> = (</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> − </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="2"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>/λ. Thus</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><TABLE BorderFill="3" CellSpacing="0" ColCount="3" PageBreak="Cell" RepeatHeader="true" RowCount="1"><SHAPEOBJECT InstId="1946448494" Lock="false" NumberingType="Table" TextWrap="TopAndBottom" ZOrder="142"><SIZE Height="4882" HeightRelTo="Absolute" Protect="false" Width="22650" WidthRelTo="Absolute"/><POSITION AffectLSpacing="false" AllowOverlap="false" FlowWithText="true" HoldAnchorAndSO="false" HorzAlign="Left" HorzOffset="0" HorzRelTo="Para" TreatAsChar="false" VertAlign="Top" VertOffset="0" VertRelTo="Para"/><OUTSIDEMARGIN Bottom="141" Left="141" Right="141" Top="141"/></SHAPEOBJECT><INSIDEMARGIN Bottom="141" Left="510" Right="510" Top="141"/><ROW><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="0" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="1575"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="1" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="1425"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> = </CHAR></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="2" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="19650"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>[</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="19"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>e</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> − 1)/λ + (</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="19"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>]</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>1/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> for all </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL></ROW></TABLE><CHAR/></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>An economically interesting feature of the model is the evolution of the capital-labor ratio </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>). We have</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><TABLE BorderFill="3" CellSpacing="0" ColCount="2" PageBreak="Cell" RepeatHeader="true" RowCount="1"><SHAPEOBJECT InstId="1946448495" Lock="false" NumberingType="Table" TextWrap="TopAndBottom" ZOrder="143"><SIZE Height="5610" HeightRelTo="Absolute" Protect="false" Width="21150" WidthRelTo="Absolute"/><POSITION AffectLSpacing="false" AllowOverlap="false" FlowWithText="true" HoldAnchorAndSO="false" HorzAlign="Left" HorzOffset="0" HorzRelTo="Para" TreatAsChar="false" VertAlign="Top" VertOffset="0" VertRelTo="Para"/><OUTSIDEMARGIN Bottom="141" Left="141" Right="141" Top="141"/></SHAPEOBJECT><INSIDEMARGIN Bottom="141" Left="510" Right="510" Top="141"/><ROW><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="0" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="4950"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="1" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="5046" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="16200"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><TABLE BorderFill="3" CellSpacing="0" ColCount="1" PageBreak="Cell" RepeatHeader="true" RowCount="3"><SHAPEOBJECT InstId="1946448496" Lock="false" NumberingType="Table" TextWrap="TopAndBottom" ZOrder="144"><SIZE Height="5046" HeightRelTo="Absolute" Protect="false" Width="15675" WidthRelTo="Absolute"/><POSITION AffectLSpacing="false" AllowOverlap="false" FlowWithText="true" HoldAnchorAndSO="false" HorzAlign="Left" HorzOffset="0" HorzRelTo="Para" TreatAsChar="false" VertAlign="Top" VertOffset="0" VertRelTo="Para"/><OUTSIDEMARGIN Bottom="141" Left="141" Right="141" Top="141"/></SHAPEOBJECT><INSIDEMARGIN Bottom="141" Left="510" Right="510" Top="141"/><ROW><CELL BorderFill="4" ColAddr="0" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="0" RowSpan="1" Width="15675"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>[</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="19"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>e</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR> − 1)/λ + (</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="19"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"><CHAR>]</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>1/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"/></P></PARALIST></CELL></ROW><ROW><CELL BorderFill="5" ColAddr="0" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="1" RowSpan="1" Width="15675"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="22"/></P></PARALIST></CELL></ROW><ROW><CELL BorderFill="6" ColAddr="0" ColSpan="1" Dirty="false" Editable="false" HasMargin="false" Header="false" Height="282" Protect="false" RowAddr="2" RowSpan="1" Width="15675"><PARALIST LineWrap="Break" LinkListID="0" LinkListIDNext="0" TextDirection="0" VertAlign="Center"><P ParaShape="19" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="19"><CHAR>0</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="24"><CHAR>e</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="25"><CHAR>λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="18"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="22"/></P></PARALIST></CELL></ROW></TABLE><CHAR/></TEXT></P></PARALIST></CELL></ROW></TABLE><CHAR/></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>for all </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>. As </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> grows without bound, this fraction converges to</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sA</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>/λ)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="9"><CHAR>1/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="20"><CHAR>a</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>We now have</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sG</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>), </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)).</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>As before, the labor force grows at the constant rate λ, so that</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = λ.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>We may study the behavior of the capital-labor ratio </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) as follows. Let </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> and define the function </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> of a single variable by</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, 1) for all </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Since </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> is increasing and concave we have </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>' &gt; 0 and </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>" &lt; 0, and since it is homogeneous of degree 1 we have</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>LG</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, 1) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>Lf</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>).</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Thus</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sL</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)).</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Now,</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>k'(t)<TAB/> = <TAB/>[K'(t)L(t) − K(t)L'(t)]/(L(t))2</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>         = <TAB/>[K'(t) − k(t)L'(t)]/L(t)</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>so</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sf</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)) − λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>t</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>).</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Assuming that </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sf</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(0) &gt; λ and </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sf</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) &lt; λ for large values of </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, so that the function </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sf</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) lies above the function λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> for small values of </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> and below it for large values of </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, the phase diagram of this equation is shown in the following figure.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>λkk*k →sf(k)sf(k) − λk</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><PICTURE Reverse="false"><SHAPEOBJECT InstId="1946448487" Lock="false" NumberingType="Figure" TextFlow="BothSides" TextWrap="Square" ZOrder="140"><SIZE Height="23280" HeightRelTo="Absolute" Protect="false" Width="26640" WidthRelTo="Absolute"/><POSITION AffectLSpacing="false" AllowOverlap="true" FlowWithText="true" HoldAnchorAndSO="false" HorzAlign="Left" HorzOffset="12454" HorzRelTo="Paper" TreatAsChar="false" VertAlign="Top" VertOffset="15024" VertRelTo="Paper"/><OUTSIDEMARGIN Bottom="0" Left="0" Right="0" Top="0"/><SHAPECOMMENT>그림입니다.
