원본 그림의 크기: 가로 440pixel, 세로 385pixel</SHAPECOMMENT></SHAPEOBJECT><SHAPECOMPONENT GroupLevel="0" HorzFlip="false" InstID="872706664" OriHeight="23280" OriWidth="26640" VertFlip="false" XPos="0" YPos="0"><ROTATIONINFO Angle="0" CenterX="13320" CenterY="11640"/><RENDERINGINFO><TRANSMATRIX E1="1.00000" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="1.00000" E6="0.00000"/><SCAMATRIX E1="1.00000" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="1.00000" E6="0.00000"/><ROTMATRIX E1="1.00000" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="1.00000" E6="0.00000"/></RENDERINGINFO></SHAPECOMPONENT><IMAGERECT X0="0" X1="26640" X2="26640" X3="0" Y0="0" Y1="0" Y2="23280" Y3="23280"/><IMAGECLIP Bottom="28860" Left="0" Right="33000" Top="0"/><INSIDEMARGIN Bottom="0" Left="0" Right="0" Top="0"/><IMAGE Alpha="0" BinItem="2" Bright="0" Contrast="0" Effect="RealPic"/><EFFECTS/></PICTURE><CHAR/></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"/></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><PICTURE Reverse="false"><SHAPEOBJECT InstId="2110713826" Lock="false" NumberingType="Figure" TextFlow="BothSides" TextWrap="Square" ZOrder="154"><SIZE Height="36780" HeightRelTo="Absolute" Protect="false" Width="48240" WidthRelTo="Absolute"/><POSITION AffectLSpacing="false" AllowOverlap="true" FlowWithText="true" HoldAnchorAndSO="false" HorzAlign="Left" HorzOffset="9154" HorzRelTo="Paper" TreatAsChar="false" VertAlign="Top" VertOffset="39796" VertRelTo="Paper"/><OUTSIDEMARGIN Bottom="0" Left="0" Right="0" Top="0"/><SHAPECOMMENT>그림입니다.
원본 그림의 이름: i88fC.png
원본 그림의 크기: 가로 1333pixel, 세로 1016pixel</SHAPECOMMENT></SHAPEOBJECT><SHAPECOMPONENT GroupLevel="0" HorzFlip="false" InstID="1036972003" OriHeight="36780" OriWidth="48240" VertFlip="false" XPos="0" YPos="0"><ROTATIONINFO Angle="0" CenterX="24120" CenterY="18390"/><RENDERINGINFO><TRANSMATRIX E1="1.00000" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="1.00000" E6="0.00000"/><SCAMATRIX E1="1.00000" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="1.00000" E6="0.00000"/><ROTMATRIX E1="1.00000" E2="0.00000" E3="0.00000" E4="0.00000" E5="1.00000" E6="0.00000"/></RENDERINGINFO></SHAPECOMPONENT><IMAGERECT X0="0" X1="48240" X2="48240" X3="0" Y0="0" Y1="0" Y2="36780" Y3="36780"/><IMAGECLIP Bottom="76200" Left="0" Right="99960" Top="0"/><INSIDEMARGIN Bottom="0" Left="0" Right="0" Top="0"/><IMAGE Alpha="0" BinItem="1" Bright="0" Contrast="0" Effect="RealPic"/><EFFECTS/></PICTURE><CHAR/></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>We see that under these assumptions the equation has two equilibria, </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>* = 0, which is unstable, and the value of </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>* for which </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sf</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*) = λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*, which is locally stable.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>The stable equilibrium value of </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> depends on </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>: the equation</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sf</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*) = λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>implicitly defines </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>* as a function of </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>. Which value of </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> maximizes the equilibrium value of per capita consumption? Per capita consumption is equal to (1 − </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>K</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)/</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>L</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>, or, given our previous calculations, (1 − </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>). Thus in an equilibrium per capita consumption is equal to (1 − </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)). A stationary point </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>* of this function satisfies</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(1 − </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*)</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*))</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*) = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*)).</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Now, differentiating the equation defining </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>* we obtain</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>)) + </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>sf</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>))</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) = λ</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>) for all </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>Using this equation for </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> = </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>* reduces the first-order condition for the savings ratio </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>* that maximizes per capita consumption to</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="22" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>f</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>'(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>k</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*(</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>s</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>*)) = λ.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="21" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR>The </CHAR><FIELDBEGIN Command="https\://mjo.osborne.economics.utoronto.ca/index.php/tutorial/index/1/deq/HOM\#d\:hom1;1;0;0;" Dirty="true" Editable="false" InstId="1946448482" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="26"><CHAR>homogeneity of degree 1</CHAR><FIELDEND Editable="false" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> of the production function </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> </CHAR><FIELDBEGIN Command="https\://mjo.osborne.economics.utoronto.ca/index.php/tutorial/index/1/deq/HOM\#p\:HomDeriv;1;0;0;" Dirty="true" Editable="false" InstId="1946448483" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="26"><CHAR>implies that</CHAR><FIELDEND Editable="false" Property="0" Type="Hyperlink"/></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> that the derivatives of </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> are homogeneous of degree zero, which in turn implies that the left-hand side of this equation is equal to the derivative of the production function </CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="21"><CHAR>G</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="8"><CHAR> with respect to capital at the optimal amounts of capital and labor. In economic jargon, that's the marginal product of capital. Thus the result says that the marginal product of capital at the equilibrium capital-labor ratio for the optimal savings rate is equal to the rate of population growth.</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="10"><CHAR/></TEXT></P><P ColumnBreak="false" PageBreak="true" ParaShape="16" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="16" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="1"><CHAR>위상도 분석의 강점과 제약</CHAR></TEXT><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="16" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="16" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"><CHAR>위상도는 시간축이 없으므로 균형에 이르기까지 얼마나 시간이 걸리는지를 알 수 없다.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="16" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="16" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"><CHAR>위상도는 변수들의 동시 움직임을 나타내므로, 토빈의 q 이론에서 보듯이 자본량(capital stock)이 높을 때 자본의 가격은 낮다. 또는 그 역도 성립.(사소한 것이지만 기본 성장모형에서는 나타나지 않음)</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="16" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"><CHAR>조정속도는 균형경로의 모양에 따라 다를 수 있음. 가파른 경로는 빠른 수렴을, 완만한 곡선은 느린 조정속도를 의미한다.</CHAR></TEXT></P><P ParaShape="18" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P><P ParaShape="3" Style="0"><TEXT CharShape="10"/></P></SECTION></BODY><TAIL><BINDATASTORAGE><BINDATA Encoding="Base64" Id="1" Size="49185">iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAABTUAAAP4CAIAAACDTY+SAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1B
